				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I feel it uncomfortable buying my supplies from someone other than my brother dwarves. I seem to know good metal from bad and have been quite successful in building my knowledge in the crafting of metal. If I were to get the things to make armor from another race it would seem to me that they would be able to tell what I used. It would worry me that the trade secrets my mentors have taught me could be deduced from ingredients I used. It also strikes me odd that I would not learn to mine the ore in my homeland since I doubt dwarves would settle in a land that did not have these things plentiful. Mining similar to foraging would be an interesting addition to the skills since I was not blessed with many, being that I am a Dwarven Cleric. I was disappointed that I had to travel to Freeport to do most of my training in their forge since supplies are not available in my home city.
